<paragraph id="B7319717507EFFC9C278FE2EFADAFA75" blockId="51.[819,1435,389,1423]" pageId="51" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="85FA4B05507EFFC9C278FE2EFBE5FE60" box="[819,1125,389,410]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="134">Abbreviated description:</emphasis>
Length of adults 
<quantity id="70763AF2507EFFC9C278FE08FC3BFE43" box="[819,955,419,441]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="51" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.7">1.7â€“1.8 mm</quantity>
. Body parallel-sided. Head slightly longer than wide. Antenna with 11 antennomeres. Maxilla with length of lacinia subequal to length of galea, lacinia acute apically, teeth on adoral margin short, about 3 times longer than wide, and more or less widely placed, into two distinct regions; galea moderately narrow, narrower than lacinia at widest area, and truncate apically, membranous in apical 1/8, covered with few rows of short, fine hairs; maxillary palpi with 4 articles and a moderately defined pseudosegment, articles 2 and 3 with numerous long setae, articles 1, 4 and pseudosegment without setae. Labium with ligula about twice as long as wide, broadened apically with deeply forked apex, fork about 1/2 length of ligula; two long medial setae of prementum present, longer than ligula, insertion of setae almost adjacent; hypoglossal lobes moderate in length, reaching beyond base of ligula, with short, about 0.5 times width of lobe, comb-like straight setae along entire length of adoral margin. Labial palpi elongate, overall length 4â€“5 times longer than greatest width. Pronotum broadly oval, about 1.3 times wider than long. Elytra broad, together about 1.2 times wider than long; apicolateral angles sinuate. Legs with tarsal formula 4-5-5. Abdomen fusiform to parallel-sided, tapering apically to broadly pointed apex. Males variable with narrow posteromedian longitudinal carina or small denticles on tergum 
<collectionCode id="D19F0FD2507EFFC9C2F8FB4BFC51FB0F" box="[947,977,1248,1269]" pageId="51" pageNumber="134">III</collectionCode>
(?), and numerous denticles on abdominal tergum VII. Aedeagus with bulb of median lobe elongate, shorter than tube, with distinct ventral projection; internal sac with numerous, small spinules. Spermatheca more or less coiled: basal bulb, simple and rounded at base; neck, significantly curved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7319717507EFFC9C278FA0CFB6BF9CD" blockId="51.[819,1434,1447,1591]" pageId="51" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="85FA4B05507EFFC9C278FA0CFC31FA46" box="[819,945,1447,1468]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="134">Comments:</emphasis>
